@Barry Ancona -- I'm sure that having children, whether they're teachers or not, helps a great deal.  

Re EMOJIS:  My brother, who at five years younger than me is still certifiably old, often sends me EMOJIS in emails.  I have no idea why -- I've never encouraged him and I've never responded in kind.  But I say nothing about it one way or the other -- I love my brother and wouldn't want to hurt his feelings.  Besides, these would seem to be upbeat emojis so far as I can tell.  Sometimes they're part of a written message and sometimes they're standing alone.  I think they're smiling emojis, though I'm not entirely sure since, I suppose, they also could be grimacing.  Are they all the same emoji or are the ones he sends me all different?  (I enlarge and enlarge on the screen and still can't tell.)

Sometimes, though, he'll send me a simple heart emoji.  That one I really, really like -- no interpretation necessary!

